        <article><![CDATA[<p><em>Activation of the Agent Chat plugin is required in order to access the configuration page for this task.</em></p>
<p>Agents can use Rejection Reasons to denote why they are declining an assignment in their inbox. These reasons are applied to all service channels by default, but can be specified to a single channel.</p>
<p>You can review the prebuilt Reject Reasons including ‘Busy’, ‘No access’, ‘Not my expertise’, and ‘Time out’. Additionally, you can create your own Reject Reasons and define which service channels they are applied to, whether agents can select them manually, and whether the chat are reassignable afterward.</p>]]></article>
